<abstract>
<t>
DNS has a number of privacy vulnerabilities.  Query privacy
has received the most attention, with DNS-over-TLS and DNS-over-HTTPS
now standardized, and continuing work on both.  This document
addresses privacy risks to the holder of the zone, the risk that
the entire contents of the zone can be acquired in an unauthorized way
by an adversary.  The DNS action of zone transfer is protected by
an authentication key but a standard to encrypt the transfer does not
exist.  This document describes how to use TLS (TCP is already in use) for
zone transfer (AXFR) and incremental transfer (IXFR).
</t>
</abstract>


